3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"KuCoin calculates SUI/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC using the time-weighted average premium between perpetual and spot prices. The funding rate is capped at ±0.75% per interval to prevent extreme rates during high volatility periods. Long positions pay funding when rates are positive, while short positions receive payments, with settlements occurring automatically in your futures wallet."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","SUI","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"SUI's status as a Layer 1 blockchain creates distinct funding rate patterns driven by ecosystem developments, validator updates, and DeFi activity. The token's mid-tier trading volume on KuCoin generates moderate but consistent funding rate variations, offering predictable arbitrage windows for traders monitoring network fundamentals."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"SUI/USDT funding rates on KuCoin typically range from -0.1% to +0.3% per 8-hour period, with higher positive rates during ecosystem announcements or major partnership reveals. The pair shows increased funding volatility during Sui network upgrades and when new protocols launch on the blockchain. Weekend periods often see compressed funding rates due to reduced institutional activity, while weekday sessions around major timezone overlaps generate the most significant rate movements."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities and Strategy"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Optimal SUI funding rate arbitrage on KuCoin emerges when rates exceed ±0.15% per interval, accounting for the 0.02% maker and 0.06% taker fees. Cross-exchange arbitrage works well by pairing KuCoin SUI perpetuals with Binance or OKX spot holdings, especially during Sui ecosystem events when funding rates diverge significantly. The 8-hour intervals provide sufficient time to establish hedged positions, though traders should monitor SUI's correlation with broader Layer 1 tokens during market-wide moves."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management and Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"SUI's relatively newer market presence creates higher volatility risks compared to established assets, requiring careful position sizing in funding rate strategies. KuCoin's moderate SUI liquidity can lead to slippage during rapid market movements, particularly in the Asian trading session when volumes peak. Traders should account for potential funding rate caps during extreme market conditions and monitor Sui network developments that could trigger sudden sentiment shifts affecting both spot and perpetual prices."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"What are typical SUI/USDT funding rates on KuCoin?","answer":"SUI/USDT funding rates on KuCoin typically range from -0.1% to +0.3% per 8-hour period under normal market conditions. Rates tend to spike during major Sui ecosystem announcements or broader Layer 1 rallies, occasionally reaching the ±0.75% cap."},{"question":"How does KuCoin's SUI liquidity affect funding arbitrage?","answer":"KuCoin's SUI perpetual liquidity is moderate, suitable for positions up to $50,000 without significant slippage. Larger arbitrage operations may experience execution challenges during volatile periods, making position timing crucial for optimal entry and exit."},{"question":"When do SUI funding rates change on KuCoin?","answer":"SUI/USDT funding rates update every 8 hours on KuCoin at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC. The new rate applies to positions held at the settlement time, with payments processed automatically in your futures account balance."},{"question":"What drives SUI funding rate volatility on KuCoin?","answer":"SUI funding rate volatility stems from ecosystem developments, validator network changes, and new protocol launches on Sui blockchain. Market sentiment around Layer 1 competition and institutional adoption of Sui also creates significant funding rate movements, especially during major crypto conferences or partnership announcements."}]}]
